\Bbb Q(\sqrt{p}+\sqrt{q}) \subseteq \Bbb Q(\sqrt{p},\sqrt{q})
\sqrt{p}+\sqrt{q} \in \Bbb Q(\sqrt{p}+\sqrt{q})
\implies \sqrt{pq} \in \Bbb Q(\sqrt{p}+\sqrt{q})
\implies q\sqrt{p}+p\sqrt{q} \in \Bbb Q(\sqrt{p}+\sqrt{q})
\implies \sqrt{q} \in \Bbb Q(\sqrt{p}+\sqrt{q})
